a) ‘Strategically Maximized Durability’ means to make the good as strong and lasting as relevant. The materials utilized, comparatively assuming possible substitutions due to levels of scarcity or other factors, would be dynamically calculated, likely automatically by the design system, to be most conducive to an optimized durability standard. ''Durability'' <math>{t}_{d}</math> maximization. This ''durability ''<math>{t}_{d}\left({d}_{1},{d}_{2},\text{.}\text{.}\text{.},{d}_{i}\right)</math> maximization can be considered as a local optimization issue. It can be analyzed by introducing the factors <math>{d}_{i}</math> which affect it where <math>{d}_{1}^{o},{d}_{2}^{o},\text{.}\text{.}\text{.},{d}_{i}^{o}</math> are some optimal values of the factors. 

